cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about facial landmark detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a new model architecture that is more efficient than existing models, which suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using unlabeled images to improve the model's generalization capabilities, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
